                            <comment id="17073956" author="alangford" created="Thu, 2 Apr 2020 17:58:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The comments in the Javadocs are inconsistent with the behavior of the API:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://ci.apache.org/projects/flink/flink-docs-release-1.10/api/java/index.html?org/apache/flink/runtime/rest/handler/job/savepoints/SavepointHandlers.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://ci.apache.org/projects/flink/flink-docs-release-1.10/api/java/index.html?org/apache/flink/runtime/rest/handler/job/savepoints/SavepointHandlers.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Javadoc claims that the response JSON will be of the form (note that the second key of the object is &quot;savepoint&quot;):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;{&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;tt&gt;&#160; &quot;status&quot;: {&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;tt&gt;&#160; &#160; &quot;id&quot;: &quot;completed&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;tt&gt;&#160; },&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;tt&gt;&#160; &quot;savepoint&quot;: {&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;tt&gt;&#160; &#160; ...&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;}&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;tt&gt;}&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the API actually returns &quot;operation&quot; where the javadocs say &quot;savepoint&quot;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;{&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;tt&gt;&#160; &quot;status&quot;: {&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;tt&gt;&#160; &#160; &quot;id&quot;: &quot;completed&quot;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;tt&gt;&#160; },&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;tt&gt;&#160; &quot;operation&quot;: {&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;tt&gt;&#160; &#160; ...&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;}&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;tt&gt;}&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The REST API docs actually have this correct. So the javadocs need to be corrected AND the REST API docs need to be given more detail as stated in the original description.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
